            </rs>. <rs id="t17541023-33-cd163" type="crimeDate">Sept. 26</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17541023-33-off162 t17541023-33-cd163"></join>. + .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17541023-33-person228">
                  Boyce 
                  Tree 
               <interp inst="t17541023-33-person228" type="surname" value="Tree"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17541023-33-person228" type="given" value="Boyce"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17541023-33-person228" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 26th of Sept. passing by <placeName id="t17541023-33-crimeloc164">Pye Corner</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17541023-33-crimeloc164" type="placeName" value="Pye Corner"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17541023-33-crimeloc164" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17541023-33-off162 t17541023-33-crimeloc164"></join>, betwixt 11 and 12 at noon, I was surrounded by 3 or 4 fellows, I believe there were 4 of them; one of them gave me a stroke on the right arm; they jostled me, and I believe their hands were in every pocket of my coat and waistcoat. I thought I saw a glimpse of my handkerchief coming out of my pocket, by a quick motion. They separated immediately, 3 of them ran toward St. Sepulchre's church, and the prisoner toward Smithfield; I followed him; he turned up for Snow Hill; I took him in Cock Alley; I searched him and found my handkerchief in his breeches.</p>

               <p>Q. Did they say any thing to you?</p>
               <p>Tree. There was not a word spoke.</p>
               <p>Q. Was the prisoner ever out of your sight?</p>
               <p>Tree. He was when he turned up Cock Alley, but that was not for half a minute.</p>
               <p>Fra. Furner. I was at work in Cock Lane at a baker's shop, I heard Mr. Tree call out; I saw him clap his hand on the prisoner's shoulder, and heard him say, where is my handkerchief? the prisoner said, I have it not, nor know anything of it; I saw Mr. Tree find the handkerchief in the prisoner's breeches. The prisoner said a man in a leather apron gave it him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I am not guilty of picking the gentleman's<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="175410230020"></xptr> pocket myself; I am guilty of receiving it; one of them is 
               <persName id="t17541023-33-person229">
                  Samuel 
                  Sparks 
               <interp inst="t17541023-33-person229" type="surname" value="Sparks"></interp>
